    "text": "Genetic and expression analyses in two inbred populations examined the genetic control of domestication-related differences in flowering time and growth habit between domesticated chickpea and its wild progenitor Cicer reticulatum. A major QTL for flowering time under short-day conditions, DTF3A, was mapped to a 59-gene interval on chromosome three. This interval contains a cluster of three FT genes, which showed upregulated expression in domesticated parent lines relative to wild parent lines.",
